  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The applicant has failed to provide a clear and accurate description of the proposed development. In particular, the maximum height and eaves height of the extension as described on the submitted application form conflict with the submitted plans. This application therefore fails to comply with Schedule 2, Part 1, Class A, condition A.4 (1)(2)(a) of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015. \r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed extension would extend from/beyond a wall forming a side elevation of the original dwellinghouse and would have a width greater than half the width of the original dwellinghouse, thereby breaching the threshold of  Schedule 2, Part 1, Class A.1 (J) (iii) of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015; therefore, planning permission is required. "
